<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,1461,1956]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1713,1739]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is known only from the in 
<collectingCountry box="[795,906,1713,1739]" name="Argentina" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Misiones Prov.). The 
<typeStatus box="[1162,1210,1714,1740]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
locality of Loreto is the same for many other species of deltocephaline leafhoppers due, in part, to the collections made by A.A. Ogloblin (mistakenly typed Oglobin on 
<typeStatus box="[498,546,1786,1812]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
series labels and Ogoblin on labels in the series from NCSU) in the early 20 
<superScript attach="right" box="[1424,1437,1785,1799]" fontSize="6" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">th</superScript>
century.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,1461,1956]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1857,1883]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Oman, P. W." box="[323,475,1857,1883]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="343 - 420" refId="ref80707" refString="Oman, P. W. (1938) A generic revision of American Bythoscopinae and South American Jassinae. University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 37, 343 - 420." type="journal article" year="1938">
<collectingCountry box="[323,391,1857,1883]" name="Oman" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Oman</collectingCountry>
(1938)
</bibRefCitation>
