<typeStatus box="[687,797,1858,1884]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">paratypes</typeStatus>
, however only three were found at USNM in this study. The specimens borrowed from NCSU were previously unidentified. The species misidentified and figured as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Faltala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyptera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">F. brachyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
